cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.NE

This paper proposes a novel architectural component for improving the learning of deep neural networks on sequential inputs, including text and audio. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers a broad range of topics related to deep learning. Additionally, the paper specifically mentions text classification and audio super-resolution, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SD (Sound) are also likely sub-categories. The use of convolutional models and feature-wise modulations suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the paper mentions the use of a recurrent neural network, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category, although less likely than the others.
